{
  "game_explanation": "Overall, incentives are driven by private values: buffalo highly values BLUE and dislikes RED, bear values both BLUE and RED but values BLUE most, and goose values GREEN most while valuing RED and BLUE very little. That makes mutually acceptable trades most likely when buffalo offers RED for BLUE to bear, or when bear offers BLUE for GREEN to goose. Because players only know their own values, early turns likely test favorable deals, and later turns adjust to holdings after accepted exchanges.",
